# 5. あの日のわたし達

Honami: Wh-What is this place...?
Honami: It looks like a station platform... There's even a train and a set of tracks...
MEIKO: It's really something, isn't it? I was just as surprised the first time I came here.
MEIKO: Also, if you look carefully here and there, you'll notice a few odd things.
Honami: Odd things? Oh...
Honami: This train has no destination... Same with the electronic bulletin board...
MEIKO: Exactly. And look where the tracks go.
Honami: Huh? Oh...!
Honami: They extend out towards that starry sky...!
Honami: That's incredible! It's like you can ride this train to the stars...!
Len: Oh. I didn't realize you were here, Honami.
Honami: Oh, Len! I didn't know you'd be here.
Len: Yeah, I came to see what this new area's all about.
Honami: Yes, I see.
Honami: Still, why did it appear out of the blue like this...?
Len: I don't have any specifics... But I think it has to do with you and the others' feelings, Honami.
Len: After all, this SEKAI was born out of them.
Honami: Our feelings...?
Honami: But what feelings would those be...?
MEIKO: No idea. It may have to do with something that you and the others haven't realized yet.
Honami: Something we haven't realized...?
MEIKO: Huh...?
Len: Hm? What's up, MEIKO?
MEIKO: I think I see some people on the other platform. It looks like...
Honami: Huh?
Honami: ...?!
Honami: (Isn't that me...?! And Ichika...?!)
Honami: (I think they're talking about something...)
Junior High School Honami: I'm sorry, Ichika...
Junior High School Honami: Please don't talk to me at school anymore.
Honami's Voice: What...?
Junior High School Ichika: What? Why don't you want to talk to me?
Junior High School Honami: I already made up with my classmates, so you don't have to worry about me. Okay?
Junior High School Ichika: Honami, I don't get it... Wait!
Honami: Ichika...!
Honami: Ichika, wait! It's not what you think!
Len: Huh...?! Honami?!
Honami: (I don't know what our past selves are doing over there...!)
Honami: (I have no idea...)
Honami: (But I don't want Ichika to look so sad!!)
Honami: (I have to get over to that platform.)
Honami: Ichika!
Honami: Huff... Huff... She's gone...
Honami: Ichika! Where are you?!
Honami: No...
Honami: I don't want her to feel that way...
Honami: Ichika!!
Honami: What you said to me then made me so happy!!
Honami: I'd become an outcast in class...! And I absolutely dreaded going to school each day...!
Honami: But you worked up the courage to come talk to me. You showed genuine concern...!
Honami: You don't know how happy that made me!!
Honami: And yet... I couldn't find the same courage...
Honami: I'm sorry...!
Honami: I'm so sorry, Ichika...!!!
Len: Honami...!
Honami: Len, MEIKO...
Honami: I... I...
MEIKO: Honami, look over there.
Honami: Huh?
MEIKO: There. The other platform.
Honami: The other...
Honami: Oh...
Honami: (Ichika... She's smiling...?)
Honami: (That day, I caused Ichika a lot of pain...)
Honami: (I can't change that fact. And I can't ask for her forgiveness...)
Honami: (But...)
Honami: (I can change the future. If I can learn to become stronger, be more courageous and know when to act...)
Honami: (I'll be able to do more for everyone next time.)
Honami: I want to protect them...
MEIKO: See? I was right.
Honami: Huh?
MEIKO: You've become so strong.
MEIKO: You're able to put into words what you couldn't back then.
Honami: Oh...
MEIKO: So, there's no need for you to worry or feel scared.
MEIKO: Just keep moving straight forward. You'll become stronger and lead everyone in the right direction.
Honami: MEIKO...
Honami: Thank you!!
Honami: (She's right...)
Honami: (I've been able to become stronger bit by bit thanks to the others in Leo/need and everyone here in SEKAI...)
Honami: (I'm sure there'll be plenty more tough times and moments when I question myself in the future...)
Honami: (But I'm going to become stronger.)
Honami: (Because I want to keep moving forward with everyone...!!)
